Retalix Gains Most in Week as Second-Quarter Profit Rises 81%

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-08-03T13:24:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/retalix-gains-most-in-week-as-second-quarter-profit-rises-81-.html
Retalix Ltd. (RTLX)  gained the most in more
than a week after the maker of software used by supermarkets
posted second-quarter net income that rose 81 percent and said
2011 revenue was tracking to the “high end” of its outlook.  The shares climbed as much as 3 percent, the most since
July 25, and traded up 2 percent at 50.40 shekels at 3:36 p.m.
in  Tel Aviv .  “Our organically generated revenues are trending to the
high-end of our guidance for 2011,” Chief Executive Officer
Shuky Sheffer said today in a Globe Newswire statement. The
company previously said it expected 2011 revenue in a range of
$217 million to $228 million.  Net income in the second quarter increased to $2.9 million
from $1.6 million, Retalix said.  Separately, the Ra’anana, Israel-based company said its
point-of-sale, store management and loyalty products were
selected by Russian grocer  DIXY Group OJSC. (DIXY)   To contact the reporter on this story:
Susan Lerner in Jerusalem at 
